<font color="#FF0000">#6 STATION OF THE CROSS</font><br>
<tt>Fri May  2 13:39:36 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Everyone should recognize the rolling thunder<br>
in the bowels when his ETS anniversary RTs. Tomorrow,<br>
May 3rd, will be my 29th year back out in the world<br>
and still I am drawn to wonder at the smell of<br>
burnt flesh, bedpans, and the Nurses Office still in<br>
my neuronal-nose!  When I drove away from WRAMC in early May, 1968,<br>
in my 1959 gunmetal-blue Porshe and trundled towards<br>
Gloucester, Mass., to catch what was left of the<br>
West End, I could not imagine the future in its<br>
tandem, 3:00 AM dreamscapes of herded, rolled-hay<br>
swaying in the full-moon blasts like mastadons.  All<br>
the way back to Oklahoma I prayed the RTs would stay <br>
behind me.
<p><code>--   (Anonymous) </code><p>


